The paper deals with learning control in an online lifelong learning scenario, which involves both model-based planning and model-free learning. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). However, given the focus on reinforcement learning and the use of neural networks, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The other sub-categories are also relevant due to the emphasis on control and adaptation in dynamic environments.
